title: PML-N’s Manan Khan wins PP-56 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz candidate Manan Khan has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-56, Narowal-III by securing 48,889 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Haleem Tariq an independent candidate who bagged 35,617 votes.
The voters’ turnout remained 49.42 percent.
